edieval Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:11th century in Armenia]]\n[[Category:12th century in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Medieval Syria]]\n[[Category:Medieval Iraq]]\n[[Category:States in medieval Anatolia]]\n", "name_user": "Bruhhh83", "label": "safe", "comment": "seljuk empire is an oghuz turkic empire it shall have a turkish name (do not revert)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seljuk_Empire"}
{"title_page": "The Box (Roddy Ricch song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 single by Roddy Ricch}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = The Box\n| type     = single\n| artist   = [[Roddy Ricch]]\n| album    = [[Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial]]\n| released = {{Start date|mf=yes|2020|2|28}}\n| format  =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded = 2019<ref name=\"Studio Sessions\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolt.tv/2020/3/19/21186606/roddy-ricch-engineer-chris-dennis-interview|title=Studio Sessions: Chris Dennis talks Roddy Ricch recording at home due to Coronavirus, making \"The Box\", and an unreleased DaBaby collab|last1=Nelson Jr.|first1=Keith|last2=Dennis|first2=Chris|website=[[Revolt (TV network)|Revolt]]|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n| genre    = <!--Do NOT add any genres without sources or else you will be reverted on sight-->\n| length   = {{duration|m=3|s=16}}\n| label    = \n*[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n\n*Bird Vision\n| writer   =\n* [[Roddy Ricch|Rodrick Moore, Jr.]]\n* [[30 Roc|Samuel Gloade]]\n* Adarius Moragne\n* Aqeel Tate\n| producer = \n* [[30 Roc]]\n* Datboisqueeze\n* Zentachi\n| prev_title = [[Letter to Nipsey]]\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title = [[Walk Em Down]]\n| next_year  = 2020 \n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|UNZqm3dxd2w|\"The Box\"}}|type=single}}\n}}\n\"'''The Box'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Roddy Ricch]], released as the fourth single on February 28, 2020,{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} from his debut studio album ''[[Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial]]''. Prior to the song being released as a single,<ref name=\"GQ\" /><ref name=\"Vulture\" /> it became Roddy Ricch's highest-charting song worldwide, reaching number one on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]], the [[Canadian Hot 100]] and in New Zealand, as well as peaking at number two in both the UK and Ireland and reaching the top five in Australia. The song received acclaim from critics, with praise for Ricch's vocal delivery. Used in over 1.5 million videos on [[TikTok]] as of February 2020,<ref name=\"Time Viral\">{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5784337/roddy-ricch-the-box-interview/|title=Going Viral Helped Catapult Roddy Ricch and 'The Box' to #1 \u2014 But There's More to the Story|last=Lang|first=Cady|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=February 18, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> it became a popular meme, particularly due to Ricch's \"ico<!--In case clarification is needed: this does not apply to WP:PEACOCK. It is what the sources called it, as clearly cited-->nic\"<ref name=\"HNHH\" /><ref name=\"RS Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/roddy-ricch-the-box-video-959980/amp/|title=Roddy Ricch (Finally) Drops a Video for 'The Box'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Klinkenberg|first=Brendan|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> \"eee err\" [[ad libitum#Music or rhythm|ad-lib]]. A video was released on February 28, 2020, directed by Ricch.\n\n==Background and composition==\n\"The Box\" was the last song Ricch made for ''[[Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial]]''.<ref name=\"GQ\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/roddy-ricch-the-box-interview-2020|title=Chart-Topping Rapper Roddy Ricch Won't Let Superstardom Change Him|last=Schube|first=Will|date=January 24, 2020|website=[[GQ]]|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> It was recorded in roughly 15 minutes<ref name=\"Studio Sessions\" /> in the early morning hours in New York after Ricch had been recording all night.<ref name=\"GQ\" /> The song begins with a \"triumphant introduction that amounts to an orchestral swell\", which many listeners attributed as a sample of the intro on \"[[Love Sex Magic]]\" by [[Ciara]].<ref name=\"30Roc\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8548888/30-roc-interview-roddy-ricch-the-box-sample|title=30 Roc on Producing the Beat to Roddy Ricch's No. 1 Hit 'The Box' and Those Opening Strings: 'It Is Not a Sample'|last=LeDonne|first=Rob|date=January 24, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|language=en|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> However, the song's producer, [[30 Roc]], has insisted that though similar, the \"swell\" is not a sample of \"Love Sex Magic\", explaining: \"It is not a sample. It's really a VST [plug-in] using Omnisphere [production software].\"<ref name=\"30Roc\" /> Ricch said he decided to place \"The Box\" as track two on the album, because \"it just bangs [and] the [[Roland TR-808|808s]] hit so hard\".<ref name=\"Making The Box\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8547981/roddy-ricch-the-box-interview|title=Roddy Ricch Interview: Making The Box and His Chart-Topping Success|last=Lamarre|first=Carl|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song's intro contains a \"squeaky sound\", known as the \"eee err\" sound, which is also heard throughout the rest of the song. According to [[Atlantic Records]] [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] Keefa Black, after the song was finished, Ricch said \"Wait let me add something\", and came up with the sound himself.<ref>{{Cite tweet|url=https://twitter.com/KEEFABLACK/status/1214275540175114242|title=we made The Box at 6am in NYC after being up all night...|last=Keefa Black|date=January 6, 2020|user=KEEFABLACK|accessdate=February 16, 2020|number=1214275540175114242|author=Keefa Black}}</ref> Speaking on where the inspiration for the sound came from, he said \"I seen [[Michael Jackson]] do it...That's what made me want to do it. Cause he was in the studio one time and he was talking about some song that he made but he started [[beatboxing]] and he said he put that in the beat.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/roddy-ricch-the-box-sound-effects-inspired-by-michael-jackson-news.105944.html|title=Roddy Ricch \"The Box\" Sound Effects Inspired By Michael Jackson|website=HotNewHipHop|last=A.|first=Aron|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 13, 2020}}</ref> The squeaky sound has inspired many memes online.<ref name=\"OCC\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/who-is-roddy-ricch-the-rapper-taking-over-the-world-with-tik-tok-viral-song-the-box__28456/|title=Who is Roddy Ricch? The rapper taking over with viral hit The Box|date=January 24, 2020|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> [[Musicologist#Education and careers|Musicologist]] and [[Northeastern University]]  professor of music Andrew Mall said the \"eee err\" sound is not exactly the most interesting component of the song's beat, instead pointing out Ricch's skill as a songwriter: \"I'm really taken by the atmospheric [[Synthesizer|synths]] that underpin the track and provide the central [[Harmonic|harmonic component]], particularly since there is no bass to speak of aside from a pitched bass drum sample. Regarding Ricch's craft as a writer, Mall noted \"the fact that he retains writing credit here and on several other tracks that are charting, including those where he is a featured artist, speaks to a strong business savvy on his part\".<ref name=\"Time Viral\" />\n\n[[Vulture magazine|Vulture]]'s Paul Thompson said Ricch \"raps with verve\", calling the song \"strange and eccentric\", while noting Ricch's vocal versatility in the song, writing, he \"moves easily between vocal modes, sounding defiant ('''I won't ever sell my soooooouuuuuullllll, and I can back that''<nowiki/>'), conspiratorial ('<nowiki/>''Got a bitch that's looking like [[Aaliyah]] \u2014 she a model''<nowiki/>'), or playful \u2014 like when he cackles unnervingly at the beginning of the second verse\".<ref name=\"Vulture\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/roddy-ricch-the-box-explained.html|title=How Roddy Ricch\u2019s 'The Box' Just Became Rap's First Viral No. 1 Hit of 2020|last=Thompson|first=Paul|date=January 13, 2020|website=[[New_York_(magazine)#Digital_expansion_and_blogs|Vulture]]|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref> The song's title has been noted as being a possible reference to jail (\"[[Solitary confinement|the box]]\" being a slang term for \"jail\").<ref name=\"OCC\" />\n\n==Critical reception==\nAlong with the tracks \"Boom Boom Room\" and \"Start wit Me\" featuring [[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]], Darryl Robertson of ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]'' felt that \"The Box\" is \"further proof that the Atlantic Records-signee can pen addictive radio-friendly records\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/2019/12/roddy-ricc-antisocial-tour|title=Roddy Ricch Kicks Off His 'Antisocial Tour' By Selling Out L.A.'s Hollywood Palladium|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|last=Robertson|first=Darryl|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref> Josh Svetz of ''[[HipHopDX]]'' echoed a similar sentiment, writing that \"The appeal to Roddy is simple; the kid can write a hell of a hook. Whether it's the head-bopping harmony on 'The Box' or the flute backed, Gunna-assisted single, 'Start Wit Me,' Roddy excels at producing choruses that stick and only get better with repeat listens.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/reviews/id.3590/title.review-roddy-ricch-justifies-the-hype-on-please-excuse-me-for-being-antisocial|title=Review: Roddy Ricch Justifies The Hype On 'Please Excuse Me For Being Antisocial'|work=[[HipHopDX]]|last=Svetz|first=Josh|date=December 26, 2019|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'', Alphonse Pierre stated that on the song, which features a \"hard-hitting beat that sounds like a teapot is boiling in the background, [Ricch] finds a new delivery and pitch nearly every 10 seconds. The track is the best example of Roddy's versatility, which has been both a blessing and a curse.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/roddy-ricch-please-excuse-me-for-being-antisocial/|title=Roddy Ricch: Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Pierre|first=Alphonse|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nPraising the song, ''[[HotNewHipHop]]''{{'}}s&nbsp;Mitch Findlay asserted that although its [[Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial|parent album]] \"yielded plenty of highlights, none stood out quite so much as 'The Box'\". Findlay called the song's \"EEE ERR\" intro \"creative and soon-to-be-iconic\" and labeled Ricch's flow as confident and charismatic.<ref name=\"HNHH\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/roddy-ricch-celebrates-the-box-being-the-worlds-1-song-news.99757.html|title=Roddy Ricch Celebrates \"The Box\" Being The World's #1 Song|website=HotNewHipHop|last=Findlay|first=Mitch|date=January 2, 2020|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref> Heran Mamo of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' opined that Ricch \"comes armed and ready with his verses despite the rather lighthearted 'hee-hoo' ad-libs in the background\". Mamo noted that in the song, Ricch raps about acquiring and protecting \"his necessary riches\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lyrics/8546850/roddy-ricch-the-box-lyrics|title=Here Are the Lyrics to Roddy Ricch's 'The Box'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Mamo|first=Heran|date=December 19, 2019|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"The Box\" spent 11 weeks at the top spot of the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9340653/roddy-ricch-the-box-harry-styles-adore-you-hot-100|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Leads Hot 100 for 11th Week, Harry Styles' 'Adore You' Hits Top 10|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9346375/weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-hot-100|title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Doja Cat's 'Say So' Enters Top 10|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> after debuting at number 47 on the issue dated December 21, 2019, and reaching number one four weeks later, becoming Ricch's first number one on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 as well as the first new song to top the chart in the 2020s decade (since both \"[[All I Want for Christmas Is You]]\" by [[Mariah Carey]] and \"[[Circles (Post Malone song)|Circles]]\" by [[Post Malone]] began their runs at the top position in 2019). During the same week, the song logged its second week at number one on ''Billboard''{{'}}s [[Streaming Songs]] chart (drawing 68.2 million streams) and jumped to number eight on the [[Digital Songs]] chart as well, with 11,000 downloads sold. Additionally, the song reached the top spot on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] and [[Hot Rap Songs]] charts as well, becoming Ricch's first number-one song on both charts.<ref name=\"Hot 100\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8547900/roddy-ricch-the-box-hot-100-number-one|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Bounds to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Justin Bieber's 'Yummy' Debuts at No. 2|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=January 13, 2020|accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe song's audio video was released on December 6, 2019, while a lyric video premiered on January 9, 2020,<ref name=\"Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8549337/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-week-three|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Billboard Hot 100 For Third Week; Eminem, Juice WRLD's 'Godzilla' Roars In at No. 3|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=January 27, 2020|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref> accumulating over 180 million and 20 million views on YouTube, respectively, as of April 2020.\n\nThe song's official music video was released on February 28, 2020 and has over 88 million views as of April 2020. It was directed by Ricch, with co-direction by Christian Breslauer, who also directed Ricch's previous two music videos, for \"Boom Boom Room\" and \"Tip Toe\".<ref name=\"EW Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/roddy-ricch-finally-drops-the-box-music-video/|title=Roddy Ricch finally drops 'The Box' music video after seven weeks atop the charts|last=Jones|first=Marcus|website=[[Entertainment Weekly|EW.com]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MTV Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mtv.ca/roddy-ricch-the-box-video/|title=Roddy Ricch Dunks, Races, And Dances In His Long-Awaited Video For 'The Box'|last=Roth|first=Madeline|date=February 28, 2020|website=[[MTV News|MTV Canada]]|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref> Ricch explained via [[Twitter]] the reason why the video took a \"lil time\" to be released was because he directed it.<ref>{{Cite tweet|url=https://twitter.com/RoddyRicch/status/1233606444936658944?s=19|title=it took me a lil time cause i directed it but the box music video out now...|number=1233606444936658944|user=RoddyRicch|author=Roddy Ricch|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Synopsis and concept===\nThe \"action-packed\"<ref name=\"MTV Video\" /><ref name=\"XXL Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2020/02/roddy-ricch-the-box-video/|title=Roddy Ricch Drops \"The Box\" video: Watch|work=[[XXL Magazine|XXL]]|last=Fitzgerald|first=Trent|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> video starts with Ricch speeding in a \"super charged\" [[muscle car]]<ref name=\"XXL Video\" /> in a\u00a0\"''[[Fast & Furious]]''-style [[Street racing|street race]]\".<ref name=\"MTV Video\" />  During the race, Ricch turns on his [[turbocharger|turbos]] and \"outdrives his opponent who eventually crashes and burns, leaving Ricch the victor of the contest\".<ref name=\"XXL Video\" /> The video then cuts to a basketball game, where Ricch is seen scoring the game-winning shot, \"flying\" in the air, akin to NBA icon [[Michael Jordan]],<ref name=\"XXL Video\" /> with what [[MTV News|MTV]]'s Madeline Roth called an \"impressive (and definitely far-fetched)\" [[slam dunk]].<ref name=\"MTV Video\" /> Ricch is then seen carrying out a major [[bank heist]].<ref name=\"XXL Video\" /> Multiple scenes reference the song's lyrics, such as when Ricch delivers a speech from the [[White House]],<ref name=\"MTV Video\" /> alluding to the line \"''I'm a 2020 presidential candidate''\". Halle Kiefer of [[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]] noted a theme in the video: \"the visual follows Ricch's unstoppable success as it takes him to surreal lengths, whether it be lounging on a bed suspended over sharks, casually walking up the side of a building or dancing in front of an explosive game of chicken\".<ref name=\"Vulture Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/rapper-roddy-ricch-releases-the-box-music-video-watch.html|title=Roddy Ricch Is the One to Beat in His New 'The Box' Music Video|last=Kiefer|first=Halle|date=February 28, 2020|website=[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]]|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref> The video concludes with Ricch inside a glass box, \"preserved for future generations inside a museum exhibit\".<ref name=\"Vulture Video\" />\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/124616525|title=Please Excuse Me For Being Antisocial / Roddy Ricch|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Roddy Ricch]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting\n* [[30 Roc]] \u2013 songwriting, production\n* Datboisqueeze \u2013 songwriting, production\n* Zentachi \u2013 songwriting, additional production\n* Chris Dennis \u2013 recording\n* Curtis \"Sircut\" Bye \u2013 engineering assistant\n* Cyrus \"NOIS\" Taghipour \u2013 mixing\n* [[Derek Ali|Derek \"MixedByAli\" Ali]] \u2013 mixing\n* Nicolas de Porcel \u2013 mastering\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardargentinahot100|54|artist=Roddy Ricch|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|4|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 8, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|10|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|12|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|16|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|1|artist=Roddy Ricch|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 23, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|3|year=2020|week=04|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 28, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=5&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 5, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n| 4\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|4|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=8?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 8, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|12|songid=1930552|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|publisher=[[IFPI Greece]]|accessdate=1 March 2020|title=Official IFPI Charts \u2013 Digital Singles Chart (International) \u2013 Week: 7/2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|13|year=2020|week=4|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|1|year=2020|week=12|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Iceland ([[Music of Iceland|Tonlist]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plotutidindi.is/lagalistinn/|title=T\u00d3NLISTINN \u2013 Vika 2 \u2013 2020; Pl\u00f6tut\u00ed\u00f0indi}}</ref>\n| 15\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|2|date=20200124|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 25, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/3/2020/5|title=Top Singoli \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 5|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>\n| 34\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Malaysia ([[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|RIM]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RecordingIndustryMalaysia/photos/pcb.3201821669845181/3201807546513260/?type=3&theater|title=Top 20 Most Streamed International & Domestic Singles In Malaysia|language=English|work=[[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia]]|publisher=Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|accessdate=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n| 11\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|4|artist=Roddy Ricch|song=The Box|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=4815|title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=February 3, 2020|accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Norway ([[VG-lista]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://topplista.no/charts/singles/2020-w04/|title=Singel 2020-W04|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate