{"title_page": "Travis Way", "text_new": "{{short description|American male curler and coach}}\n{{Infobox curler\n| name = Travis Way\n| gender = M\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|4|30}}\n| birth_place = \n| Curling club = [[Granite Curling Club (Seattle)|Granite CC]], [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|WA]]\n| Skip = \n| Third = \n| Second = \n| Lead = \n| Alternate = \n| Mixed doubles partner = \n| Member Association = {{USA}}\n| World Championship appearances = 1 ({{WMCC|2001}})\n| World Mixed Doubles Championship appearances = \n| European Championship appearances = \n| Olympic appearances = \n| Other appearances = {{WJCC||World Junior Championships}}: 1 ({{WJCC|1996}})\n| show-medals = yes\n| medaltemplates=\n{{MedalSport | [[Curling]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[United States Men's Curling Championship|United States Men's Championship]] }}\n{{MedalGold | 2001 Madison | }}\n}}\n\n'''Travis Way''' (born April 30, 1975) is an [[United States|American]] [[curling|curler]] and curling [[coach (sport)|coach]].<ref>{{worldcurling}}</ref>\n\nAt the national level, he is a 2001 [[United States Men's Curling Championship|United States men's champion]] curler.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.madisoncurlingclub.com/nationals/news/rel26.htm|title=Illinois, Washington rinks win USA Curling Nationals|last=|first=|date=Mar 2, 2001|website=Madison Curling Club|url-status=dead|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20010723223427/http://www.madisoncurlingclub.com/nationals/news/rel26.htm|archive-date=Jul 23, 2001|access-date=Apr 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n*USA Curling Male Athlete of the Year: 1996.<ref>[https://www.teamusa.org/USA-Curling/For-Athletes/Awards/Male-Athlete-of-the-Year Male Athlete of the Year - USA Curling]</ref>\n\n==Teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!width=\"60\"|Season!!Skip!!Third!!Second!!Lead!!Alternate<br>''<small>Coach</small>''!!Events\n|-\n| 1995\u201396 || '''Travis Way''' || [[Troy Schroeder]] || Owen Bunstine || [[Brandon Way]] || [[Matt Stevens (curler)|Matt Stevens]] (WJCC) || [[United States Junior Curling Championships|USJCC]] 1996 {{Gold1}}<br>{{WJCC|1996|WJCC 1996}} (6th)\n|-\n| 1996\u201397 || [[Ian Cordner]] || Rodger Schnee || '''Travis Way''' || Owen Bunstine || || \n|-\n| 1998\u201399 || [[Jason Larway]] || '''Trawis Way''' || [[Joel Larway]] || [[Tom Violette]] || || \n|-\n| 1999\u201300 || [[Tim Somerville]] || [[Mike Schneeberger]] || '''Trawis Way''' || [[John Gordon (curler)|John Gordon]] || || \n|-\n| 2000\u201301 || [[Jason Larway]] || [[Greg Romaniuk]] || '''Travis Way''' || [[Joel Larway]] || [[Doug Kauffman]]<br>''<small>[[Jack McNelly]]</small>'' || [[United States Men's Curling Championship|USMCC]] 2001 {{Gold1}}<br>{{WMCC|2001|WCC 2001}} (6th)\n|}\n\n==Record as a coach of national teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Tournament, event !! National team !! Place\n|-\n| 2014 || [[2014 World Junior Curling Championships]] || {{USA}} (junior men) ||<center>9</center>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{sports links}}\n*{{curlingzone}}\n<!--*[https://teamvukich.wordpress.com/ www.TeamVukich.com | USA Junior Curling Team from Seattle, Washington]-->\n*{{facebook|TeamVukich|Team Vukich}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Way, Travis}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:American male curlers]]\n[[Category:American curling champions]]\n[[Category:American curling coaches]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Seattle metropolitan area]]\n\n\n{{US-curling-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American male curler and coach}}\n{{Infobox curler\n| name = Travis Way\n| gender = M\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|4|30}}\n| birth_place = \n| Curling club = [[Granite Curling Club (Seattle)|Granite CC]], [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|WA]]\n| Skip = \n| Third = \n| Second = \n| Lead = \n| Alternate = \n| Mixed doubles partner = \n| Member Asso