 must remember this': Autobiography as social critique.\" ''Journal of American History'' (1998): 439\u201365 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2567747 in JSTOR].\n* {{cite journal |last=Hattaway |first=Herman |date=Summer 1971 |title=Clio's Southern Soldiers: The United Confederate Veterans and History |journal=Louisiana History |publisher=Louisiana State University |volume=XII |issue=3 |pages=213\u201342}}\n* {{cite book|last=Janney|first=Caroline E.|title=Burying the dead but not the past: Ladies' Memorial Associations and the lost cause|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P4AOGGLcfy8C&pg=PA39|accessdate=January 24, 2012|year=2008|publisher=U of North Carolina P|isbn=978-0-8078-3176-2}}\n* Janney, Caroline E. \"The Lost Cause.\" [http://www.encyclopediavirginia.org/Lost_Cause_The ''Encyclopedia Virginia'' (Virginia Foundation for the Humanities, 2009)]\n* {{cite book|editor1-last=Loewen|editor1-first=James W.|editor1-link=James W. Loewen|editor2-last=Sebesta|editor2-first=Edward H.|title=The Confederate and Neo-Confederate Reader: The \"Great Truth\" about the \"Lost Cause\"|date=2010|publisher=University Press of Mississippi|location=Jackson|isbn=978-1-60473-218-4}}\n* Osterweis, Rollin G. ''The Myth of the Lost Cause, 1865\u20131900'' (1973) [https://www.questia.com/library/101494599/the-myth-of-the-lost-cause-1865-1900 online]\n* Reardon, Carol, ''Pickett's Charge in History and Memory'', University of North Carolina Press, 1997, {{ISBN|0-8078-2379-1}}.\n* {{cite book|last1=Simpson|first1=John A.|title=Edith D. Pope and Her Nashville Friends: Guardians of the Lost Cause in the Confederate Veteran|date=2003|publisher=University of Tennessee Press|location=Knoxville, Tennessee|isbn=9781572332119|oclc=750779185}}\n* Stampp, Kenneth. ''The Causes of the Civil War.'' (3rd edition 1991)\n* Ulbrich, David, \"Lost Cause\", ''Encyclopedia of the American Civil War: A Political, Social, and Military History'', Heidler, David S., and Heidler, Jeanne T., eds., W. W. Norton 